1 as a long - time fan of studio ghibli and especially hayao miyazaki films , i went to the film right on the opening day . when i went out of the theater i had this strange feeling that something was missing , this " magical " feeling i was experiencing in all miyazaki films before , but i could n't say why it failed this time . after i thought about the other ghibli movies , i may know the reason : this film had most of the elements of a great miyazaki anime : cute characters , wonderful key animation , a great soundtrack composed by joe hisaishi and the warm story telling giving you the feeling of watching a high quality japanese animation film . however , two elements were lacking : a deep story and dramaturgy . the purpose of this film was obviously to entertain small children with a simple story line as in case of " totoro " , so a complicated story as been told in " spirited away " or " princess mononoke " is not really necessary , but on the other hand , this story was simply too superficial . i could not connect to the main characters , because there was no character development , dramatic scenes were only limited and did not last very long . i really hate to give only 7 stars for a miyazaki film , because i would give 10 stars to all previous movies right away , but this time it was simply not this wonderful " ghibli experience " .
