1 like all of the very earliest films , this " movie " is very , very short -- lasting about one minute ! so , because of its brevity , it 's not really possible to compare it to more modern films . but , for its time , it 's actually a very remarkable film . much of this is because the prints were hand painted -- making annabelle appear red and other colors as she does her amazing dance . i 've actually seen two different versions -- one where she is red and another where she changes color throughout . i think the red one depicted on the dvd " the great train robbery and other primary works " is the best of them . the dance itself is very hypnotic and much like a piece of amazing performance art . and , unlike other one minute ( or less ) films of the day , this one is one i could see repeatedly -- it 's just that visually compelling and odd.<br /><br />if you want to see it online , there is a 36 second version on google video ( type in " serpentine dance " ) .
