0 the bbc and the arts & entertainment network should be ashamed of themselves for foisting this unfortunate production onto the world . the acting is , with the exception of robert hardy as general tilney , amateurish at best and excruciatingly painful at worst . the costumes are over - the - top and feature some truly ghoulish excesses -- was the costume designer obsessed with feathers for women 's hats ? surely every woman in bath did n't have feathers in her headpiece in the early 19th century . the production values are poor and the pacing of the film makes one feel it was hastily and clumsily edited at the last minute . altogether an agonizing film that i had to force myself to watch to the end . it 's a shame , as the producers obviously spent a lot of money on costumes and location shooting . compared to emma thompson 's sublime " sense and sensibility " or the extraordinary 1995 production of " pride and prejudice " or the subtle intensity of 1995 's " persuasion " , this production of ` northanger abbey ' surely has jane austen turning in her grave .
