tural . the saving grace are seema biswas and the young girl . they are fabulous.<br /><br />and this was a period film - but the hindi dialogues suck big time . even there utterance is also as unnatural as it gets . no rustic accents ! ! ! no local slangs . no nothing . the only thing right was probably the shooting locales . i thought that the set of the vidhwa - ashram was reasonably real . the overall blue tinge in the whole movie is also apt.<br /><br />but all and all , do n't watch this movie . you _ wo n't _ get anything . there is nothing in the story , or direction . if you have to watch it watch it for the little girl 's acting .
